column6: This subclass includes:- information dissemination, public relations, fund-raising and similar services provided by political parties and similar organizations, engaged in placing their members or those sympathetic to the party in political offices

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9599. Services furnished by other membership organizations n.e.c.
column5: Services furnished by other membership organizations n.e.c.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95991. Services furnished by human rights organizations
column5: Services furnished by human rights organizations
column6: This subclass includes:- services provided by membership organizations for the purpose of furthering human rights, such as citizen initiative or protest movements, by means of information dissemination, political influence, fund-raising etc.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95992. Services furnished by environmental advocacy groups
column5: Services furnished by environmental advocacy groups
column6: This subclass includes:- services provided by membership organizations for the purpose of furthering environmental protection, by means of information dissemination, political influence, fund-raising etc., such as by environmental, conservation or wildlife organizations

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95993. Other special group advocacy services
column5: Other special group advocacy services
column6: This subclass includes:- services provided by associations for the protection and betterment of special groups, such as disability, ethnic and minority groups by means of public education, political influence, the support of community and social activities and facilities, etc.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95994. Other civic betterment and community facility support services
column5: Other civic betterment and community facility support services
column6: This subclass includes:- other services provided by membership organizations for the purpose of furthering a public cause or issue by means of public education, political influence, etc.- services provided by patriotic associations, including war veterans' associations- other services provided by organizations in support of community, social and educational activities and facilities

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95995. Services provided by youth associations
column5: Services provided by youth associations
column6: This subclass includes:- services provided by associations of young people and children- services provided by student associations, clubs and fraternities- services provided by associations, such as boy or girl scouts etc.This subclass does not include:- accommodation services of student dormitories and student fraternities, cf. 63210

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95996. Grant-giving services
column5: Grant-giving services
column6: This subclass includes:- grant-giving services by membership organizations or foundations, typically to fund activities for education, research or general community or social interestThis subclass does not include:- credit granting, cf. 7113

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95997. Cultural and recreational associations (other than sports or games)
column5: Cultural and recreational associations (other than sports or games)
column6: This subclass includes:- associations for the pursuit of a cultural or recreational activity or hobby (other than sports or games), e.g., poetry, literature and book clubs, historical clubs, gardening clubs, film and photo clubs, music and art clubs, craft and collectors' clubs, social clubs, carnival clubs etc.This subclass does not include:- services of professional artistic organizations, cf. 962- services of sports clubs, cf. 96512

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95998. Other civic and social organizations
column5: Other civic and social organizations
column6: This subclass includes:- services provided by consumer associations- services provided by automobile associations- services provided by associations for the purpose of social acquaintanceship, such as rotary clubs, lodges etc.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 95999. Other services provided by membership organizations n.e.c.
column5: Other services provided by membership organizations n.e.c.
column6: This subclass includes:- services provided by homeowners' associations and tenants' associations (other than advocacy)- services provided by membership organizations n.e.c.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96. Recreational, cultural and sporting services
column5: Recreational, cultural and sporting services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 961. Audiovisual and related services
column5: Audiovisual and related services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9611. Sound recording services
column5: Sound recording services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96111. Sound recording services, except live recording services
column5: Sound recording services, except live recording services
column6: This subclass includes:- services rendered in the process of converting sounds, words, and music to a permanent physical format using the specialized technical equipment of a sound recording studioThis subclass does not include:- reproduction of audio recordings, on a fee or contract basis, cf. 89123- live recordings done outside a studio, such as at a concert hall, stadium, outdoor stage, or conference centre, cf. 96112- providing a sound recording studio or sound recording equipment where the client provides the primary technicians and operators of the equipment, cf. 73129

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96112. Live recording services
column5: Live recording services
column6: This subclass includes:- all recording services performed on location of a live, public event, such as a conference, seminar, meeting, or concert, etc.- recording of live radio broadcasts done within a sound recording studioThis subclass does not include:- sound recording services performed in a studio, cf. 96111

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96113. Sound recording originals
column5: Sound recording originals
column6: This subclass includes:- original recordings of sounds, words and music converted to a digital or analogue format

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9612. Motion picture, videotape, television and radio programme production services
column5: Motion picture, videotape, television and radio programme production services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96121. Motion picture, videotape and television programme production services
column5: Motion picture, videotape and television programme production services
column6: This subclass includes:- production and realization of motion pictures including animated cartoons primarily designed for showing in movie theatres- production and realization of motion pictures of all types (e.g., series, telefilms, including animated cartoons) primarily designed for showing on television- production and realization of promotional or advertising motion pictures- production of television programmes, live or recordedThis subclass does not include:- production services of still and slide films, cf. 8381

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96122. Radio programme production services
column5: Radio programme production services
column6: This subclass includes:- production of radio programmes, live or recorded

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96123. Motion picture, videotape, television and radio programme originals
column5: Motion picture, videotape, television and radio programme originals
column6: This subclass includes:- copyrighted motion picture, videotape, television and radio programmes produced without contract for outright sale (i.e. with all-attendant property rights)Note: These originals are produced for sale that is implicitly or explicitly protected by copyright.This subclass does not include:- production of motion pictures, television and radio programmes under contract for others, cf. 96121, 96122

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9613. Audiovisual post-production services
column5: Audiovisual post-production services
column6: This class includes:- providing computerized and electronic image and sound processing services for audiovisual works (produced on film, video, or digital media, etc.), such as editing, transfer, colour correction, digital restoration, visual effects, animation, format conversion, compression and digital encoding, captioning, titling, subtitling, sound editing and design services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96131. Audiovisual editing services
column5: Audiovisual editing services
column6: This subclass includes:- organizing and arranging the visual and audio aspects of an audiovisual work (produced on film, video, digital media, etc.) by analyzing, evaluating, and selecting scenes in terms of story continuity and dramatic and entertainment value, using equipment such as viewers, projectors, and digital video editing devices and techniques - incorporating stock shots selected from film and video libraries into film or video

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96132. Transfers and duplication of masters services
column5: Transfers and duplication of masters services
column6: This subclass includes:- transfers services, i.e. transferring an audiovisual work (produced on motion picture film, video, digital media, etc.) from one format to another with the purpose of adapting the production to a format selected for its presentation or preservation characteristics (e.g., creating backup masters or copies because the original is deteriorating). Examples include transfer of film to tape, tape to film, digital media to film, digital media to tape, diapose to video, photo to video, etc.- duplication and copying services for audiovisual works, except film, i.e. creating large-run and small-run reproductions of audiovisual works (video, digital media, etc.) for a variety of uses. The reproductions may be produced in a variety of formats, including VHS, DVD, streaming video, etc.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96133. Colour correction and digital restoration services
column5: Colour correction and digital restoration services
column6: This subclass includes:- colour correction services, i.e. adding, modifying, or excluding colour of audiovisual works (produced on film, video, or digital media, etc.) electronically, using digital techniques- digital restoration services for audiovisual works, i.e. removing scratches from audiovisual works (produced on film, video, or digital media, etc.) by using digital techniques to get the film ready for the transfer process

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96134. Visual effects services
column5: Visual effects services
column6: This subclass includes:- introducing visual effects to audiovisual works (produced on film, video, or digital media, etc.) by applying photographic or digital technology to the work after the principal photography or main shooting has occurred, such as miniatures, optical and digital effects, matte paintings, double printing, fades, and vignetting

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96135. Animation services
column5: Animation services
column6: This subclass includes:- creating pictures, abstract designs and similar elements for an audiovisual work using animation techniques, such as computerized animation, sequences of drawings, or claymation (animation of personages and objects created with clay)

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96136. Captioning, titling and subtitling services
column5: Captioning, titling and subtitling services
column6: This subclass includes:- captioning services for audiovisual works, i.e. adding text to an audiovisual work (produced on film, video, or digital media, etc.), using a character generator or a captioning data generation system, including:* open captioning services, which create text always visible on screen* closed captioning services, which create text made visible on screen at the option of the user- titling services for audiovisual works, i.e. adding typesetter and graphical elements that serve to identify and enhance the audiovisual work (film, video, or digital media, etc.) through texts, including beginning titles, credits, and words- subtitling services for audiovisual works, i.e. inserting text in the screen that translates the dialogues and titles of the original audiovisual work (produced on film, video, or digital media, etc.) to the language of the country in which the films or video is exhibited

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96137. Sound editing and design services
column5: Sound editing and design services
column6: This subclass includes:- creating, adding and recording the sound elements (dialogue, music, sounds and silences) of an audiovisual work (produced on film, video, digital media etc.) for a soundtrack that synchronizes the audio with the visual portion of the work:* composing, recording, mixing, and integrating original music and sound into the soundtrack of an audiovisual work* recording of music that is timed to the sequence of an audiovisual work* mixing and recording licensed and client-supplied music and sound for integration into the soundtrack of an audiovisual work* integrating licensed and client-supplied music and sound into the soundtrack of an audiovisual work and synchronizing the sound elements with visual elements of the work- licensing and/or agent services for licensing of music and sound bundled with mixing or integration services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96139. Other post-production services
column5: Other post-production services
column6: This subclass includes:- other postproduction services for audiovisual works (produced on film, video, digital media etc.), including format conversion services, compression services etc.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9614. Motion picture, videotape and television programme distribution services
column5: Motion picture, videotape and television programme distribution services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96140. Motion picture, videotape and television programme distribution services
column5: Motion picture, videotape and television programme distribution services
column6: This subclass includes:- distribution of audiovisual works, including granting permission to exhibit, broadcast and rent audiovisual works that are implicitly or explicitly protected by a copyright owned or controlled by the licensor, usually intended for theatres, television, home video market etc., such as:* live action or animated films* videos* digital media, etc. - management services for motion picture rightsNote: This product is transacted between the distributor and the exhibitor, television network, television station, video rental store etc.This subclass does not include:- licensing services (by the copyright holder) for the right to reproduce, distribute or incorporate audiovisual originals, cf. 73320

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9615. Motion picture projection services
column5: Motion picture projection services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96150. Motion picture projection services
column5: Motion picture projection services
column6: This subclass includes:- motion picture, videotape and similar projection services (analogue or digital) in movie theatres, in open air or in cine-clubs, in private screening rooms or other projection facilities

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 962. Performing arts and other live entertainment event presentation and promotion services
column5: Performing arts and other live entertainment event presentation and promotion services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9621. Performing arts event promotion and organization services
column5: Performing arts event promotion and organization services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96210. Performing arts event promotion and organization services
column5: Performing arts event promotion and organization services
column6: This subclass includes:- promotion and organization services for:* theatre, opera, ballet, musical and concert performances* "sound and light" performances* puppet shows* fireworks* circus performances

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9622. Performing arts event production and presentation services
column5: Performing arts event production and presentation services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96220. Performing arts event production and presentation services
column5: Performing arts event production and presentation services
column6: This subclass includes:- production and presentation services for:* theatre, opera, ballet, musical and concert performances* puppet shows* circus performancesThis subclass does not include:- production and presentation services for "sound and light" performances or fireworks, cf. 96990

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9623. Performing arts facility operation services
column5: Performing arts facility operation services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96230. Performing arts facility operation services
column5: Performing arts facility operation services
column6: This subclass includes:- operation of concert halls, theatres, opera houses, music halls- operation of multipurpose centres and of similar facilities with a cultural predominanceThis subclass does not include:- services of operating stadiums and arenas used for a variety of purposes, cf. 96520

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9629. Other performing arts and live entertainment services
column5: Other performing arts and live entertainment services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96290. Other performing arts and live entertainment services
column5: Other performing arts and live entertainment services
column6: This subclass includes:- management services for rights attached to artistic, literary, musical works, except cinematographic and audiovisual works- services ancillary to entertainment not elsewhere classified, such as:* operation of scenery and backdrops* operation of lighting and sound equipment for the performing artsThis subclass does not include:- services of personal theatrical or artistic agents, cf. 85999

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 963. Services of performing and other artists
column5: Services of performing and other artists

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9631. Services of performing artists
column5: Services of performing artists

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96310. Services of performing artists
column5: Services of performing artists
column6: This subclass includes:- services of actors, readers, singers, musicians, dancers, stunt people, television personality hosts/presenters and other performing artists- services of independent models

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9632. Services of authors, composers, sculptors and other artists, except performing artists
column5: Services of authors, composers, sculptors and other artists, except performing artists

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96320. Services of authors, composers, sculptors and other artists, except performing artists
column5: Services of authors, composers, sculptors and other artists, except performing artists
column6: This subclass includes:- services of authors, composers, sculptors- services of stage designers, set designers, lighting designers, costume designers- restoration services for works of art

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9633. Original works of authors, composers and other artists except performing artists, painters and sculptors
column5: Original works of authors, composers and other artists except performing artists, painters and sculptors

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96330. Original works of authors, composers and other artists except performing artists, painters and sculptors
column5: Original works of authors, composers and other artists except performing artists, painters and sculptors
column6: This subclass includes:- original works of:* authors, i.e. book manuscripts* composers, i.e. the original score of music, not the copyrighted master recording produced from it* other artists other than performing artists, painters and sculptorsNote: The creation of these original works is done on own account, i.e. their production is intended for sale without either a contract or known buyer in mind.This subclass does not include:- original works of painters and sculptors, cf. 38961

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 964. Museum and preservation services
column5: Museum and preservation services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9641. Museum and preservation services of historical sites and buildings
column5: Museum and preservation services of historical sites and buildings

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96411. Museum services except for historical sites and buildings
column5: Museum services except for historical sites and buildings
column6: This subclass includes:- display services of collections of all kinds (art, science and technology, history)- management and conservation services for such collections- organization of travelling exhibitions for such collectionsThis subclass does not include:- sale and display services furnished by commercial art galleries, cf. 62299- services of historical sites and buildings, cf. 96412- services of botanical and zoological gardens, cf. 96421

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96412. Preservation services of historical sites and buildings
column5: Preservation services of historical sites and buildings
column6: This subclass includes:- operation of historical sites, monuments and buildings, including access and visiting services- preservation services for historical sites, monuments and buildings

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 9642. Botanical, zoological and nature reserve services
column5: Botanical, zoological and nature reserve services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96421. Botanical and zoological garden services
column5: Botanical and zoological garden services
column6: This subclass includes:- operation of botanical and zoological gardens, including access and visiting services- conservation and maintenance services of botanical and zoological gardensThis subclass does not include:- services of nature reserves, cf. 96422

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 96422. Nature reserve services including wildlife preservation services
column5: Nature reserve services including wildlife preservation services

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 33311. Motor gasoline
column5: Motor gasoline
column6: This subclass includes:- motor gasoline, i.e. a mixture of some aromatics (e.g., benzene and toluene) and aliphatic hydrocarbons in the C5 to C12 range, with a distillation range of 25ºC to 220ºC.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 33312. Aviation gasoline
column5: Aviation gasoline
column6: This subclass includes:- gasoline prepared especially for aviation piston engines with additives which assure performance under flight conditions. Aviation gasolines are predominantly alkylates (obtained by combining C4 and C5 isoparaffins with C3, C4 and C5 olefins) with the possible addition of more aromatic components including toluene. The distillation range is 25ºC to 170ºC.

CPC21Code21ExplanatoryNote: 0426. Other pelagic fish, live, fresh or chilled
column5: Other pelagic fish, live, fresh or chilled
column6: This class includes herrings (Clupea harengus, Clupea pallasii), sardines (Sardina pilchardus, Sardinops spp.), sardinella (Sardinella spp.), brisling or sprats (Sprattus sprattus), mackerel (Scomber scombrus, Scomber australasicus, Scomber japonicus), jack and horse mackerel (Trachurus spp.), cobia (Rachycentron canadum) and swordfish (Xiphias gladius) and other pelagic fish, not included in 0425, live, fresh and chilled.This class does not include:- other live pelagic fish for ornamental purposes, cf. 0411- other live pelagic fish not for human consumption, including seeds and feeds for aquaculture, cf. 0419- other frozen pelagic fish, cf. 21216- processed products of freshwater fish, such as:* fresh and chilled fish fillets and fish meat (whether minced or not), cf. 21221* fresh or chilled fish liver and roes, cf. 21225
